description:
Reporting to the automations manager you will be in charge of the following duties:
•	Assist in controls and automation designs for projects related to the Water and Waste water industry;
•	Preparation of project documentation including FDS and OMM’s;
•	Design and programming of PLC control systems;
•	Design and implementation of HMI’s and SCADA systems;
•	Design and implementation of Telemetry systems;
•	Testing of control panels and automation systems including FAT and SAT;
•	Work on own initiative on smaller projects and work as part of a team on larger projects;
•	Liaise with the clients and Project Managers;
•	Liaise with system vendors to source automated solutions;
•	Support, design and development of the company’s Web Based (Netrix) monitoring system;
•	Technical support to company’s sites, Industrial customers and Local Authorities;
•	Tendering small projects.

Reporting to the automations manager

travel required
